<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-30T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-30T07:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/1365:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-30T15:00:00+03:00">December
                                    30, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 30—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1159. Counselor of the French Embassy told me yesterday in strict
                            confidence that he and his Ambassador had come to the conclusion that
                            the German Government is desirous of seeing a rupture of diplomatic
                            relations between France, Great Britain and the United States and the
                            Soviet Union<note n="20" xml:id="d493fn20">Presumably over the question
                                of the Soviet Union’s attack on Finland. See <ref target="#pg_952">pp. 952</ref> ff.</note> because of the obvious advantages to
                            Germany which would result therefrom.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>